    <text type="letter"> 
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.02343.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>The Illustrated American.</name>
                    <name type="place">Bible House, Astor Place,<lb/>New York, N. Y.</name>
                    <name type="place">45 Rue Vivienne,<lb/>Paris.</name>
                    <name type="place">142 Dearborn Street,<lb/>Chicago, Ill.</name>
                    <name type="place">New York,</name>
                    <date when="1890-04-02"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>April 2 <handShift rend="printed"/>18<handShift rend="manuscript"/>90.<ptr target="loc.02343_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Walt Whitman, Esq.</salute> 
                <salute><handShift rend="printed"/>Dear Sir:—</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>We have asked a number of the most prominent bachelors in the country to answer the
                question "why am I a Bachelor?" with the purpose of publishing a symposium on the
                subject in an early number of "The Illustrated American."<ptr target="loc.02343_n2"/></p>
            <p>We should highly esteem a contribution from your pen, and the favor will be doubled
                if you can send it at your early convenience.</p> 
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours very truly,</salute>
                <signed><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Maurice M. Minton</signed>
                <signed><handShift rend="manuscript"/>General Manager</signed>
                <signed><handShift rend="manuscript"/>A. L.</signed>
            </closer>
